# Git Commit Rules for Cursor

## Commit Message Format
```
ACF-### type: Brief description

- Detail 1
- Detail 2

Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
```

## Types
- `feat` - New feature
- `fix` - Bug fix
- `refactor` - Code restructuring
- `test` - Adding/updating tests
- `docs` - Documentation
- `chore` - Maintenance
- `style` - Formatting

## Rules
- Every commit references a story ID (ACF-###)
- First line under 72 characters
- Use imperative mood ("Add feature" not "Added feature")
- Explain why, not just what

## Branch Naming
- `feature/ACF-###-description`
- `bugfix/ACF-###-description`
- `hotfix/ACF-###-description`

